Types of Meat
Beef, mutton, pork as human foods. Modern abattoirs, typical layout and
features, Ante- mortem handling and design of handling facilities;
stunning methods; steps in slaughtering and dressing; and inspection;
inedible by-products; effects of processing on meat tenderization;
abattoir equipment and utilities.
Processing technologies
Chilling and freezing of carcass and meat; canning, pickling, curing and
smoking; prepared meat products like salami, kebabs, sausages;
intermediate moisture and dried meat products; radiation processing,
canning of meat
